Syntax: key('operator', root.var, index.key, item-ID{,vc.exp}) {then|else statement.block}

Description: The key statement locates an item using a B-tree index key and returns the item in a variable. This provides the ability to sequentially search the items in the file based on the index.

Parameters: root.var - Indicates the B-tree root FID associated with the target index. It must be initialized by the root statement and must be defined prior to using the key statement.

Syntax: lock lock.num{then|else statement.block}

Description: The lock statement sets one of 992 execution locks. This prevents re-entry to the program, allowing only one process to run the program at any given time.

Parameter: lock.num - Specifies the line number (from 0 to 991) to lock. If lock.num is greater than 991, the result is divided by 992, and the lock number is equal to the remainder of the equation.

on...gosub statement
Syntax: on exp gosub statement.label{, statement.label...}
Description: The on... gosub statement transfers control to a local subroutine designated by a specific statement label according to the positional value returned by the expression. If required, the exp is truncated to an integer. The program executes the local subroutine at the statement.label that corresponds to exp. For example, if the expression evaluates to 1, the first subroutine is executed.

on...goto statement
Syntax: on exp goto statement.label{, statement.label...}
Description: The on...goto statement transfers control to the line within the FlashBASIC or BASIC program that begins with the specified statement label, according to the positional value of the expression referenced by exp. The on...goto is identical to the on...gosub, except there is no return required.

open statement
Syntax: open {"{dict}",} file.ref{to file.var} {then|else statement.block}
Parameter: dict - Specifies opening the dictionary level of the specified file.var and assigning it to file.var. The optional dict can be expressed as part of the file name as dict file.var.

page statement
Syntax: page {num.exp}
Parameter: num.exp - Optional expression used to change the current value of the page number.

readv statement
Syntax: readv{u} var from {file.var,} ID.exp, ac.exp{locked statement.block}{then|else statement.block}
Description: The readvu form tests if the item is already locked and locks the item if it is not. The item lock set by readvu prevents the item from being read using the readvu statement or updated by other processes while the lock is set. If the readvu form is specified and no locked clause is present, the program pauses (and beeps continuously) at the locked item until it is available. The item lock is only released by a release, delete, or writev statement.

subroutine statement
Syntax: subroutine {(arg.list)}
subroutine subroutine.name{(arg.list)}
Description: The subroutine statement defines a program as an external subroutine. The subroutine statement must appear on the first line of an external subroutine invoked by a call statement. Arguments defined in the argument list are delimited by commas. All external subroutines must be cataloged prior to execution.

Syntax: $DEFINE identifier {replacement-text}

Description: The $DEFINE directive supplies replacement text for a symbol and defines a symbol used to control the compilation of the program. When used to replace symbol text, the specified identifier and any associated replacement text is added to the symbol table. Every occurrence of the symbol following the $DEFINE directive is replaced by the replacement text. If no replacement text is specified, the symbol is defined with a value of null.

Parameter: identifier - Specifies the symbol to be defined. replacement-text - Specifies a string of characters that the compiler uses to replace each occurrence of the symbol in the current program.

Syntax: $options {tag}

Description: The $options directive sets compatibility options for the FlashBASIC or BASIC compiler.

Parameter: EXT/DEFAULT - Extended. Provides as many statements and functions as are available. This is the default setting. Use as the new development default setting. AP - Provides code compatibility with previous releases (provided new features are not used). PICK/R83 - Pick System's R83. Currently the same as AP.

